<p><strong><span style="color: rgb(41, 105, 176);">STEP 1:</span>&nbsp;</strong>Select <strong>all&nbsp;the&nbsp;relations</strong>  that you think are <strong>expressed in this sentence</strong> between the <strong>two highlighted terms</strong>.</p>

<ul>
  <li><em>Hover over each relation to see an <strong>example sentence</strong> where the relation is expressed.</em></li>

  <li><em>Choose&nbsp;<strong>only</strong>&nbsp;the&nbsp;relations&nbsp;that&nbsp;are&nbsp;<strong>explicitly&nbsp;expressed</strong>&nbsp;in&nbsp;this&nbsp;sentence&nbsp;.</em></li>

  <li><em>If&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong>terms</strong>&nbsp;appears&nbsp;multiple&nbsp;times&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;sentence&nbsp;you&nbsp;need&nbsp;to&nbsp;consider&nbsp;<strong>only&nbsp;the&nbsp;highlighted&nbsp;words</strong>.</em></li>
</ul>

<p><span style="color: rgb(41, 105, 176);"><strong>STEP 2a:</strong></span> Highlight the words from the text that support or indicate that the selected <strong>relation</strong> holds in this sentence.<em>&nbsp;</em>To highlight text:</p>

<ul>
  <li><em>click&nbsp;on&nbsp;each&nbsp;word&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;text&nbsp;that&nbsp;you&nbsp;want&nbsp;to <strong>select</strong></em></li>

  <li><em>click&nbsp;on an already&nbsp;highlighted&nbsp;word&nbsp;to <strong>de-select</strong> it</em></li>
</ul>

<p><span style="color: rgb(41, 105, 176);"><strong>STEP 2b:</strong></span> If you select ‘<strong>NONE of the above</strong>’ in STEP 1, then explain why do you think there is no relationship between the two words in the sentence.</p>

